[[Category:Mathematical terminology]] [[Category:Topology]]

In [[mathematics]], a '''fake 4-ball''' is a [[compactness (topology)|compact]] [[contractible]] topological [[4-manifold]].  [[Michael Freedman]] proved that every three-dimensional [[homology sphere]] bounds a fake 4-ball.  His construction involves the use of [[Casson handle]]s and so does not work in the smooth category.

